      • read

        public byte[] read(int expectedLen,
                   int timeout)
            throws DeviceException
        Reading data from serial devices. The data sent by the dock to POS will be cached in the dock service first. Dock service simulates the data buffer of serial port, which currently opens up 10KB of space. When APP calls read, the dock service reads data from the cache based on the expectedLen. The actual size of the read is based on the size of the buffer returned, while the read data is cleared from the buffer of dock service. If there is no data at the time of reading, it will wait for the timeout time. If the timeout time is up and there is no data, it will return 0 bytes of data.
        Parameters:
        expectedLen - Data Length Expected to Read
        timeout - The timeout time of reading data, unit: milliseconds (ms), 0 means no waiting
        Returns:
        If timeout, or no data, it will return null.
        Throws:
        DeviceException

      • write

        public void write(byte[] sendData,
                  int timeout)
           throws DeviceException
        Write data to dock serial device. The data is sent to the dock, which does not respond to this, and the transmission is successful by default.
        Parameters:
        sendData - Data to be sent
        timeout - The timeout time of writing data, unit: milliseconds (ms), 0 means no waiting
        Throws:
        DeviceException
